Sequence Information.Peptide Name: AS-14 (synthetic AMPs AS-18 analog, Lys-rich; XXA, UCLL1c)

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (77.78%) toAS-18obtained by continued C-terminal sequence truncation of AS-18. K: 36%; L=F=R: 14%.Activity: active against E. coli ATCC 25922 or 4 clinical strains (MIC 16-32 ug/ml), P. aeruginosa ATCC 27853 or 4 clinical strrains (MIC 8-64 ug/ml),  K. pneumoniae ATCC 13883 (MIC 64-128 ug/ml), A. baumannii (MIC 64 ug/ml), Gram+ S. aureus ATCC 29213 (MIC 16 ug/ml), MRSA (MIC 16 ug/ml), S.epidermidis (MIC >128 ug/ml), and C. albicans (MIC 8 ug/ml) ATCC 10231 >128 ug/ml.
Literature Information.Author: Zhang M, Wang J, Li C, Wu S, Liu W, Zhou C, Ma L.2024
Literature Information.Title: Cathelicidin AS-12W Derived from the Alligator sinensis and Its Antimicrobial Activity Against Drug-Resistant Gram-Negative Bacteria In Vitro and In Vivo.
